WEBVTT

00:01.302 --> 00:03.304
**

00:03.704 --> 00:07.275
[ Horn blares ]

00:07.275 --> 00:09.677
[ Microphone feedback ]
We are gathered here
this day

00:09.677 --> 00:13.847
to honor a hero with a special
Bellenus Medal of Honor

00:13.847 --> 00:18.052
for Valiant Efforts in Regards
to Helping Citizens of Bellenus.

00:18.052 --> 00:20.521
Ooh. I might be
getting an award today.

00:20.521 --> 00:21.355
I didn't realize.

00:21.355 --> 00:22.923
But as we will learn,

00:22.923 --> 00:25.959
a hero may not
be handsome, couth,

00:25.959 --> 00:30.298
or even endowed
with basic intelligence.

00:30.298 --> 00:34.068
Luckily, our hero
is all of these things.

00:34.068 --> 00:38.106
On this day,
we commend Eros Bellenus.

00:38.106 --> 00:41.075
[ Cheers and applause ]

00:46.114 --> 00:47.415
[ Microphone feedback ]
You know,

00:47.415 --> 00:49.817
I almost didn't
make it here today.

00:49.817 --> 00:51.285
But with my father ailing,

00:51.285 --> 00:53.454
I have been called to duty --

00:53.454 --> 00:56.957
called to the throne.
[ Cheers and applause ]

00:56.957 --> 00:59.093
But a king must have a wife,

00:59.093 --> 01:01.329
thus my first order of business
will be

01:01.329 --> 01:04.398
to acquire
the legendary Ring of Aventia.

01:04.398 --> 01:08.136
[ Cheers and applause ]

01:08.136 --> 01:09.570
[ Gasps ]
He has a knife!

01:10.638 --> 01:13.107
Oh. Were you, uh,
looking for this?

01:13.107 --> 01:14.408
[ Thwack, thud ]

01:14.408 --> 01:16.910
Don't worry, everybody.
I-I've got the --

01:16.910 --> 01:18.412
[ Knife clinks ]

01:18.412 --> 01:20.781
**

01:22.316 --> 01:28.356
* Here comes Apollo Gauntlet

01:28.356 --> 01:31.159
[ Dance music playing ]

01:36.530 --> 01:38.599
[ Slurps ]

01:38.599 --> 01:40.501
[ Slurps ]

01:40.501 --> 01:41.669
Oh, D-Daphne,

01:41.669 --> 01:44.172
uh, how are you, uh --
How's it going?

01:44.172 --> 01:46.640
Didn't know you were gonna
be here tonight.

01:46.640 --> 01:49.510
I was going to say,
just for the record,

01:49.510 --> 01:52.012
I think you should have received
a medal today, as well.

01:52.012 --> 01:53.481
M-Medals shmedals.

01:53.481 --> 01:55.783
I-I mean, I don't do this
for the accolades.

01:55.783 --> 01:56.884
[ Eros laughs ]

01:56.884 --> 01:58.686
Oh, you're terrible.

01:58.686 --> 02:00.621
[ Slurps ]

02:00.621 --> 02:02.790
The king thought it would
undermine the value of the award

02:02.790 --> 02:05.393
if one were given
to a vigilante.

02:05.393 --> 02:07.861
Wait, the king called me
a vigilante?

02:07.861 --> 02:10.531
Oh, my God. This -- This is
the greatest day of my life.

02:10.531 --> 02:12.733
I mean, you know,
being a hero's fine,

02:12.733 --> 02:15.135
don't get me wrong,
but "vigilante"?

02:15.135 --> 02:16.504
Yeah.

02:16.504 --> 02:18.872
Only thing is,
as a vigilante...

02:18.872 --> 02:21.509
[ Raspy voice ] You g-- You got
to talk like this.

02:21.509 --> 02:23.311
I'm gonna clean up
these streets.

02:23.311 --> 02:26.214
You got to talk
like Nick Nolte.

02:26.214 --> 02:28.882
[ Normal voice ] Do -- do
you think those guys that
get community service

02:28.882 --> 02:29.883
talk like that?

02:29.883 --> 02:31.385
You know, he's --

02:31.385 --> 02:33.221
The guy's got
the orange jumpsuit on,

02:33.221 --> 02:34.988
the pokey stick,
and he's like...

02:34.988 --> 02:37.191
[ Raspy voice ] I'm gonna
clean up these streets.

02:37.191 --> 02:38.826
It is court-mandated,

02:38.826 --> 02:41.929
but, you know,
that's beside the point.

02:41.929 --> 02:44.097
[ Laughs ]

02:44.097 --> 02:46.700
Um, can I ask you
a big favor?

02:46.700 --> 02:47.901
Yes'm?

02:47.901 --> 02:50.070
Can you keep an eye
on Prince Orenthal tonight?

02:50.070 --> 02:51.339
I'm just concerned.

02:51.339 --> 02:52.540
Orenthal's really upset

02:52.540 --> 02:54.242
about Eros returning
to claim the throne.

02:54.242 --> 02:56.677
[ Chuckles ]
And he can be moody.

02:56.677 --> 02:59.780
Okay, y-yeah. I'll do it.
That -- That's fine.

02:59.780 --> 03:01.449
Thanks, Apollo.

03:04.117 --> 03:06.587
[ Slurping ]

03:06.587 --> 03:09.423
[ Insects chirping,
music stops ]

03:10.924 --> 03:13.026
[ Rooster crows ]

03:13.026 --> 03:16.397
**

03:20.033 --> 03:22.102
"Frampton Comes Alive!"

03:22.102 --> 03:24.238
What the hell happened
last night?

03:24.238 --> 03:28.242
Well, I told you not to do
anything I wouldn't do.

03:28.242 --> 03:30.244
And?

03:30.244 --> 03:31.445
You did.

03:31.445 --> 03:33.947
[ Thunder crashes ]

03:33.947 --> 03:35.316
[ Door clanks ]

03:35.316 --> 03:37.251
Where's Prince Orenthal?

03:37.251 --> 03:39.287
Hmm.
Uh...

03:39.287 --> 03:42.323
H-Hey, hey, Todd, uh,
where's Prince Orenthal?

03:42.323 --> 03:43.824
Apologies, but, uh,

03:43.824 --> 03:46.460
he drank us all under the table,
your eminence.

03:46.460 --> 03:49.129
Apollo, he didn't come home
last night.

03:49.129 --> 03:51.332
What's the last thing
you remember?

03:51.332 --> 03:52.633
[ Harp strums ]

03:52.633 --> 03:54.001
[ Slurring ]
It's not too late.

03:54.001 --> 03:57.505
If I do something heroic,
something amazing,

03:57.505 --> 03:59.940
I could still be king.

03:59.940 --> 04:02.343
Yes, king.
You. Yes.

04:02.343 --> 04:03.611
The ring!

04:03.611 --> 04:06.113
I'll find
the Ring of Aventia!

04:06.113 --> 04:08.816
Ring. Find.
Yes, find it.

04:08.816 --> 04:10.418
Yes.

04:10.418 --> 04:12.953
I g-- I guess
he went looking for

04:12.953 --> 04:14.855
the -- the Ring of Aventia.

04:14.855 --> 04:15.923
-[ Gasps ]
-What?

04:15.923 --> 04:17.325
The ring.

04:19.427 --> 04:20.961
Eros: Here we are --

04:20.961 --> 04:23.664
the deadly Caves of Chronos.
[ Crow caws ]

04:23.664 --> 04:25.766
[ Gasps ]
This is Prince Orenthal's.

04:25.766 --> 04:26.834
He is here.

04:26.834 --> 04:29.837
Orenthal wears a necklace
with a mirror on it?

04:29.837 --> 04:31.772
He's had it
since he was a baby.

04:31.772 --> 04:32.640
[ Stifled laugh ]

04:32.640 --> 04:34.007
Whatever you do,
don't laugh.

04:34.007 --> 04:36.944
Uh, this would be
the worst possible time

04:36.944 --> 04:38.211
to think about...

04:38.211 --> 04:39.847
Vanity Smurf.

04:39.847 --> 04:41.682
[ Cries ]

04:41.682 --> 04:44.552
Don't worry, Apollo.
We'll find him.

04:44.552 --> 04:46.119
[ Muffled ] I know.
I just --

04:46.119 --> 04:48.656
I just feel so guilty,
you know?

04:48.656 --> 04:52.225
Stop fiddling around.
We've got to find him.

04:55.396 --> 04:56.897
It's a maze.

04:56.897 --> 04:58.532
Keep your hand
on the right wall,

04:58.532 --> 04:59.800
and we won't get lost.

04:59.800 --> 05:04.037
Uh, yeah,
everyone knows that, doy.

05:04.037 --> 05:07.875
**

05:11.244 --> 05:13.881
[ Water dripping ]

05:21.389 --> 05:23.223
[ Screech in distance ]
Huh?

05:23.223 --> 05:26.594
[ Monkeys screeching ]

05:28.095 --> 05:29.830
[ Speaks indistinctly ]

05:29.830 --> 05:31.164
Aah!

05:31.164 --> 05:32.766
[ Screams ]

05:35.035 --> 05:36.770
[ Grunting ]

05:38.406 --> 05:41.041
[ Laser zapping ]

05:41.041 --> 05:42.443
Eros: Get off me!

05:46.847 --> 05:47.948
Apollo: Oh, no.

05:47.948 --> 05:49.016
They're all so small,

05:49.016 --> 05:52.352
but in unison,
they're able to lift me.

05:52.352 --> 05:54.187
I always knew
this was how I'd go.

05:54.187 --> 05:56.457
[ Grunting ]

06:00.060 --> 06:02.430
[ Screams ]

06:02.430 --> 06:04.598
Light! --
Hit them with light!

06:04.598 --> 06:06.133
Do you want light?
Here comes some light.

06:06.133 --> 06:07.935
Right here.
[ Bang ]

06:07.935 --> 06:09.803
[ Rock crumbling ]

06:09.803 --> 06:11.905
[ Screams ]

06:13.641 --> 06:15.743
[ Thud ]

06:15.743 --> 06:18.412
[ Groans ] I haven't
had a landing that hard

06:18.412 --> 06:20.814
since Air Koryo.

06:23.283 --> 06:25.385
Wait, Daphne --
Uh, careful.

06:25.385 --> 06:27.320
I think I know
what this is.

06:29.457 --> 06:31.892
[ Bowling pin rolls,
arrows fly ]

06:33.293 --> 06:36.329
[ Fire hisses ]

06:36.329 --> 06:38.231
How are we gonna
get through all of that?

06:38.231 --> 06:41.068
Well, I-I should be able
to synchronize my movements

06:41.068 --> 06:43.837
to a routine I learned
in hip-hop dance class.

06:43.837 --> 06:45.072
Excuse me?

06:45.072 --> 06:46.907
You're gonna provide the music
though, right?

06:46.907 --> 06:48.842
Wait,
what are we doing?
Kick it.

06:48.842 --> 06:50.343
[ Rapping ]
* Watch me whip my way

06:50.343 --> 06:51.679
* As I'm dodging
through the traps *

06:51.679 --> 06:53.146
* 'Cause there ain't
no competition *

06:53.146 --> 06:54.515
* When traps meets raps

06:54.515 --> 06:55.983
* I'm ducking and dancing

06:55.983 --> 06:58.786
* Oops, almost caught a lance
in my guts, ay *

06:58.786 --> 07:00.521
* Which would have
disemboweled me *

07:00.521 --> 07:03.190
* But here I am,
and I'm almost through *

07:03.190 --> 07:05.826
* Trying not to get killed
is what I like to do *

07:05.826 --> 07:07.127
* And when I make it,
shit *

07:07.127 --> 07:08.996
* Ain't even thinking,
shit *

07:08.996 --> 07:11.532
* Everyone take a moment
just to please apprec-- *

07:11.532 --> 07:13.801
[ Rocks clatter ]

07:13.801 --> 07:16.504
Look -- Orenthal didn't
come through here.

07:16.504 --> 07:18.105
Of course he didn't.

07:18.105 --> 07:19.840
What do you mean?

07:19.840 --> 07:22.142
He didn't even make it
out of the maze.

07:22.142 --> 07:25.045
I saw one of his gloves
down another path.

07:25.045 --> 07:26.847
[ Chuckles ]

07:26.847 --> 07:29.650
Desperate men
begin to place markers

07:29.650 --> 07:32.686
when they realize
they're hopelessly lost.

07:32.686 --> 07:36.023
Yeah,
we got a 51-50 here.

07:36.023 --> 07:37.625
[ Over radio ]
That's a big 10-4.

07:37.625 --> 07:38.959
So your obsession
with this ring

07:38.959 --> 07:40.728
is more important
than your brother's life?

07:40.728 --> 07:43.731
Oh, it's much bigger
than that.

07:43.731 --> 07:45.032
This is about restoring

07:45.032 --> 07:47.334
the Bellenus family name
to its glory.

07:47.334 --> 07:51.572
You really want to fall on
the right side of this, Daphne.

07:51.572 --> 07:53.473
Are you threatening me?

07:53.473 --> 07:54.908
Quite the opposite.

07:54.908 --> 07:57.711
I'm saying
you could still be quee--

07:57.711 --> 08:00.981
All right, I-I think that's
enough, Francis Dolarhyde.

08:00.981 --> 08:03.050
Let's -- let's calm down
for a second, here,

08:03.050 --> 08:04.718
and think this through,
okay?

08:04.718 --> 08:07.387
Hmm.
I think...not!

08:07.387 --> 08:09.690
[ Laser zaps ]
Aah! Ugh.

08:09.690 --> 08:12.059
Leave a message,
and I'll call you back.

08:12.059 --> 08:13.594
You shall see, Daphne.

08:13.594 --> 08:17.164
The magic of the ring
will be our conduit.

08:20.534 --> 08:22.402
[ Gasps ]
The ring!

08:22.402 --> 08:24.237
[ Twinkle ]
[ Laughs ]

08:24.237 --> 08:26.273
Oh, no. He's gone insane.
I got to stop him.

08:26.273 --> 08:31.545
[ Auto-tuned ] * Make
these gauntlets powerful *

08:31.545 --> 08:33.046
[ Warble ]

08:36.349 --> 08:38.251
[ Groaning ]

08:38.251 --> 08:39.587
[ Laser zapping ]

08:41.421 --> 08:42.455
[ Warble ]

08:42.455 --> 08:43.523
[ Screams ]

08:43.523 --> 08:45.058
[ Splat ]

08:45.926 --> 08:47.227
Oof.

08:47.227 --> 08:51.031
I'm guessing this'll be
a closed-casket-type situation.

08:51.031 --> 08:52.966
-[ Roars ]
-Whoa! Jesus.

08:52.966 --> 08:55.535
[ Moans ]

09:01.609 --> 09:02.475
[ Warble ]

09:02.475 --> 09:03.376
[ Thwack ]

09:03.376 --> 09:07.280
[ Screams ]

09:07.280 --> 09:11.551
[ Water dripping ]

09:11.551 --> 09:13.386
[ Thwack ]
[ Roars ]

09:13.386 --> 09:14.888
[ Twinkle ]

09:14.888 --> 09:16.089
[ Splat ]

09:16.089 --> 09:17.557
[ Footsteps ]

09:17.557 --> 09:18.726
Apollo!

09:18.726 --> 09:20.794
You defeated
the protector of the ring.

09:20.794 --> 09:25.132
And look --
the Ring of Aventia.

09:25.132 --> 09:26.634
Take it.

09:26.634 --> 09:29.469
Anyway,
we better find Orenthal.

09:32.472 --> 09:36.143
**

09:47.655 --> 09:49.356
[ Sobs, sniffles ]

09:49.356 --> 09:52.159
I've made
a terrible mistake.

09:52.159 --> 09:53.994
Oh, Daphne!

09:53.994 --> 09:58.165
I thought for once
I could be the people's hero.

09:58.165 --> 10:01.669
Eros will have such a laugh
at this one.

10:01.669 --> 10:04.638
He'll simply explode.

10:04.638 --> 10:07.007
King Bellenus: With sad heart,

10:07.007 --> 10:11.178
I must announce the passing
of my son Eros.

10:11.178 --> 10:14.815
Rumors abound about
how his demise came to pass,

10:14.815 --> 10:18.618
but I believe [sobs]
that he was killed

10:18.618 --> 10:23.857
while attempting to save the
life of his brother, Orenthal,

10:23.857 --> 10:26.860
who somehow
came out of the mishap

10:26.860 --> 10:29.529
[angrily]
completely unscathed.

10:30.563 --> 10:32.800
I'll kill you.

10:32.800 --> 10:34.501
I'll kill you!

10:34.501 --> 10:36.704
I'll kill you!
I'll kill you!

10:36.704 --> 10:38.138
Aah!
[ Grunts ]

10:38.138 --> 10:39.840
Unhand me!
Treason!
Ooh.

10:39.840 --> 10:41.875
So much for restoring
the Bellenus family name...

10:41.875 --> 10:44.411
[ King Bellenus sobbing ]
...to its former glory.

10:44.411 --> 10:48.248
**
